  <abstract>This handwritten document describes how Pvt. John F. Blair, Co. G, 128th Inf Regt., 32nd Div., World War, 1914-1918, was shot in the right thigh during the Meuse-Argonne Offensive. The offensive began on September 26, 1918 and lasted until the Armistice. Blair describes how he tried to seek shelter in a shell hole. He was hit and " Every thing turned darke (sic) for me." He went on to describe how parts of his equipments were damaged and that he was only hit by one piece of shrapnel.</abstract>
